Package: garry
Title: Lazy, Spatial-Aware Raster Arrays with JIT-Compiled Kernels
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Hugh", "Graham", email = "hugh@belian.earth", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Experimental. Lazy raster arrays with CRS/transform-aware
    semantics, chunked execution via mirai, and JIT-compiled kernels via
    anvl (XLA). Compute graph IR is R-native; GDAL handles IO via
    gdalraster; grid math via vaster.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends:
    R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    S7,
    vaster,
    gdalraster,
    mirai
Remotes:
    hypertidy/vaster@63ba4759e9f018ce89af2aa68a4059ac89ed7958,
    r-xla/anvl@b724533
Suggests:
    anvl,
